After reading the reviews I decided to punch it up a bit. I used a variety of dried wild mushrooms, lemon grass, lots of ginger in big chunks and szechuan peppercorns. After steeping the mushrooms; drained, rinsed and chopped (strained the broth) added the extra ingredients into the broth and simmered so the flavors meld & deepen. Extracted the lemon grass, ginger and peppercorms; added tofu & thickening sauce. Great soup. Reminds me of my fav chinese restaurant. Only gave 2 forks because it appears to be a starting base.

