Rating: 4
After 3 times I finally got this recipe just perfect. My changes: increase broth to 6 c. and use vegetable, substitute Woodear mushrooms for more traditional soup, decrease vinegar to 4TBS, increase cornstarch to 3 TBS, increase sesame oil to 3 TBS, skip the noodles, increase soy sauce to 3 TBS, substitute sambal oelek (ground fresh chili paste) for the red peppers (I usually add more at the table). The first time I followed the recipe exactly and found it bland, but good enough to work with. Now it's restaurant quality, I think.

