Rating: 4
With a few modifications this is the best, and easiest, hot & sour soup around. The amount of broth is ridiculously low. You could easily double the broth and use the same amount of tofu and mushrooms. The noodles are a bad idea, skip them. Cut back on the cornstarch, one Tbsp. works. Too avoid a purely brown concoction, throw in some frozen peas for color, they really add to the presentation. I also added sliced bamboo shoots which was a nice touch.

Rating: 4
This soup has become a standard in our household for its healing properties. The ginger, shiitake, tofu, chicken stock and chilies are all tonics for an ailing body, particularly helpful for colds and flu. Also, it is extremely delicious if adjustments are made. I increase the broth to 6 cups, which thins the consistency. I substitute 4 oz. sauteed fresh shiitakes, use 5 tbsp ginger, add the juice of 1 lemon, and use chili paste instead of dried flakes. You may want to try cooked, minced chicken if you're not a tofu fan. Garnish with plenty of chopped cilantro and a thin slice of lemon.

